    <stitle>Body Builder Electrical Data Book for Models Built Starting March 1, 2007 - Work Light and Outside Cab Power
        Features - In-Cab Lighting
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>In-Cab Lighting</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Standard Panel Light Dimmer Connection</title>
            <para>
                <emph type="boldundersc">FEATURE CODE DESCRIPTION:</emph>
            </para>
            <para>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM 12-Volt, Standard Equipment</para>
            <para>
                <emph type="boldundersc">FEATURE / BODY FUNCTION:</emph>
            </para>
            <para>This standard connection provides a fused connection point (5 AMPS maximum for all circuits connected
                to this point) to allow auxiliary lights to be dimmed as the panel lights are dimmed.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>This circuit utilizes a Pulse Width Modulated (PWM) signal. Do not connect a relay coil to
                        it.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>
                <emph type="boldundersc">SOFTWARE FEATURE CODES / PROGRAMMABLE PARAMETERS:</emph>
            </para>
            <para>Software Feature Codes that must be added: NONE</para>
            <para>Software Feature Codes that must be removed: NONE</para>
            <para>
                <emph type="boldundersc">WIRING INFORMATION:</emph>
            </para>
            <para>The connection is located under the instrument panel left of the interior fuse panel.</para>
            <figure id="f7300082" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg73/G73000AQ.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="472px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption></caption>
            </figure>
            <para>To connect to this circuit, remove the lock from the wire side of the bus bar connector and insert the
                added wire with terminal (terminal part number 1661208C1) on an unused connection point.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The cover opposite the wires should also be removed to verify that the new connection is
                        properly seated.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <para>Re-install the cover and lock.</para>
            <para>
                <emph type="boldundersc">TESTING:</emph>
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check that the added circuit properly dims when the panel dimmer switch is activated
                    with the headlamp switch in the PARK or ON position.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
